<p
className={`w-element c309ipl c1v90cn6 c115nxwc c1lwn44j c1fjww6l`}>
{"In Wilmington, roof replacements for townhomes typically range from $7,000 to $9,800, while larger single-family homes start around $10,500 and can go up to $16,500 depending on the size and materials. Licensed roof repairs usually cost between $900 and $2,500, depending on the scope of damage. Monthly financing options are available—starting at around $150 for smaller jobs and up to $235 for full premium replacements. For a more accurate estimate, try our roofing cost calculator."}
</p>
